Key Match Events: Jasprit Bumrah shone on his return with two wickets for 24 runs.
Ravi Bishnoi took two wickets for 23 runs.
Barry McCarthy scored 51 not out off 33 balls.
India were 47 for 2 in 6.5 overs when rain interrupted the game.
India won by 2 runs via DLS method.
Pre-Game Insights: India skipper Jasprit Bumrah won the toss and opted to bowl first.
Jasprit Bumrah returned to international cricket after an 11-month injury lay-off.
Rinku Singh and Prasidh Krishna made their debuts for India.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Rain interrupted the game and eventually forced it to be called off.
The match was played at The Village, Malahide, Dublin.
